Diagnosis.
Third anterolateral tooth absent or reduced as slight elevation, carapace with relatively long posterolateral borders (
Fig. 10A, B, E, F
). P5 propodus slender (
Fig. 10A, B
). Large purple-pink spots on anterior two-thirds of dorsal surface of carapace (
Fig. 10A, B
; 
Campbell 1969
: fig. 1B).
